  "title": "HR & Office Manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>About Our Client</strong></u></p><p>Our client is a growing Financial Institution in Singapore. As the firm continues to build out its platform, it is hiring an experienced <strong>HR & Office Manager</strong> to oversee HR operations and office administration in a lean, regulated environment.<br /></p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Manage end-to-end HR operations including payroll, leave, CPF contributions and employee records.</li><li>Lead full-cycle recruitment and onboarding.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Singapore employment regulations and MAS requirements (Fit and Proper Criteria, RNF).</li><li>Handle EP applications, performance cycles and annual IR8A preparation.</li><li>Support audits and process improvements.</li><li>Oversee day-to-day office administration.</li></ul><p><strong></strong><br /><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree in HR, Business or related field.</li><li>Minimum 5 years’ HR operations experience, ideally in a standalone role.</li><li>Familiarity with MAS regulatory frameworks is essential.</li><li>Hands-on, organised and able to operate independently.<br /></li></ul><p><u><strong>Application Process</strong></u></p><p>Please submit your resume to <strong>Eugenia Lin</strong> at eugenia.lin@empowerpartners.sg</p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.<br /></p><p><strong>EA License No.: 24S2395</strong></p><p><strong>Registration No.: R22107070</strong></p>",
